WebService::OCI
===============

Minimal, fast client for the Oracle Cloud Infrastructure (OCI) REST API.

The hard part of OCI is correct request signing, not breadth of methods. This
distribution pairs a byte-exact API-key signer with a thin HTTP::Tiny transport
and a generic request() method that reaches any OCI endpoint - you pass the path
and parameters straight from Oracle's API reference and get back decoded JSON.
It is deliberately not an auto-generated, per-service SDK.

Includes a command-line tool, oci-rest.

QUICK START

    use WebService::OCI;
    my $oci = WebService::OCI->new(service => 'objectstorage');  # ~/.oci/config
    my $res = $oci->get('/n');                                   # your namespace
    print $res->content, "\n" if $res->is_success;

    # command line
    oci-rest get /n --service objectstorage

If you have never used OCI before, read the guide:

    perldoc WebService::OCI::Guide      # key, OCIDs, config, first call
    perldoc WebService::OCI::Cookbook   # task-oriented recipes
    perldoc WebService::OCI             # API reference
    oci-rest --help

INSTALLATION

    perl Makefile.PL
    make
    make test
    make install

DEPENDENCIES

    HTTP::Tiny, CryptX (Crypt::PK::RSA), and core modules (JSON::PP,
    Digest::SHA, Digest::MD5, MIME::Base64, Getopt::Long). IO::Socket::SSL and
    Net::SSLeay are needed for HTTPS, and Cpanel::JSON::XS is used if present.

AUTHENTICATION

    API-key (request-signing) auth only - the ~/.oci/config scheme used by the
    OCI CLI and SDKs. Instance/resource principals are out of scope.

LICENSE

    Same terms as Perl itself.
